<div id="middleInnerContent">
  <h2 align="left">special assistance</h2>
  <p align="left">SkyRush offers a range of services for passengers who require special assistance. Contact us if you need assistance with any of the services outlined here. SkyRush recommends that guests make their travel plans early to enable the airline to serve them better.</p>
  <p align="left">Any requirement for assistance/special needs must be conveyed atleast 24 hours prior to travel at 09871803333 or 1800 180 3333. The executive shall assist guests with their request accordingly.</p>
  <p align="left">Medical clearance by the airline may be required only when the airline has received information that the passenger:</p>
  <p align="left">suffers from any disease, which is believed to be actively contagious and communicable;</p>
  <p align="left">who, because of certain diseases, or incapacitation may have or develop an adverse physical condition which could have an adverse effect during flight and on safety and emergency evacuation procedures</p>
  <p align="left">would require medical attention and / or special equipment to maintain their health during the flights</p>
  <p align="left">there exists a possibility of medical condition aggravated during or because of the flight</p>
  <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <p align="left">Safety regulations stipulate that passengers with additional needs may not be seated at emergency exit rows.</p>
  <p align="left">Incubators are not permitted on board SkyRush flights due to restrictions within the aircraft.</p>
  <p></p>
  <h2 align="left">special needs:</h2>
  <div id="accordion">
    <dl id="slider">
      <dt align="left">+ Carriage of Wheelchairs (Guests with Limited Mobility &amp; Senior Citizens)</dt>
      <dd>
        <p align="left">SkyRush carries wheelchair guests free of cost for all Domestic flights and International flights originating from India. For all flights Ex Dubai we charge an amount of 210 AED ,Ex Kabul we charge USD 41,for Ex Riyadh we charge 55 SAR subject to advance booking and availability. There is a limit to the wheelchair inventory per flight hence guests are requested to request for the same at the time of booking or a minimum of 24 hours prior to the flight departure</p>
        <p align="left">Guests requiring wheelchair assistance may be classified into the following categories:</p>
        <ul>
          <li align="left">senior citizens</li>
          <li align="left">guests who are not self reliant or guests with permanently reduced mobility</li>
          <li align="left">guests temporarily incapacitated by illness/ injury/requiring post operative care</li>
        </ul>
        <ul>
          <li align="left">For passengers incapacitated by illness/ injury/requiring post operative care requiring wheelchair assistance, a fit to fly certificate (issued no less than 48 hours prior to the flight departure) must be produced on the date of travel.</li>
          <li align="left">Guests who are not self reliant (capable of taking care of all their physical needs independently in-flight) must travel with a ticketed companion for assistance. In this case medical clearance must be obtained before travelling and proof in the form of a fit to fly certificate issued by a doctor must be produced on the date of travel. The issue date of the certificate must not be more than 48 hours prior to the flight departure.</li>
          <li align="left">If guests wish to use their own wheelchair at the airport, they may use it for transferring them upto the aircraft. The wheelchair will be stored in the overhead bin or under the seat (if collapsible and if size fits)</li>
          <li align="left">Manual / Collapsible Wheelchairs on all SkyRush flights are permitted. Wheelchairs with a wet cell battery shall not be accepted. However, wheelchairs powered with non spillable battery (terminals disconnected, insulated and sealed) may be carried on SkyRush’s flight.</li>
        </ul>
      </dd>
      <dt align="left">+ Carriage of Visually/Hearing Impaired Guests:</dt>
      <dt align="left">+ Carriage of Persons Suffering from Mental Disorders or Epilepsy in Aircraft:</dt>
      <dt align="left">+ Carriage of Stretcher Case Guests</dt>
    </dl>
  </div>
  <div></div>
  <h2 align="left">special care:</h2>
  <div id="accordion">
    <dl id="slider2">
      <dt align="left">+ Carriage of Unaccompanied Minors:</dt>
      <dd>
        <ul>
          <li align="left">SkyRush will accept children aged between 5-12 years traveling alone as unaccompanied children.</li>
          <li align="left">SkyRush will charge a fee of 1500INR or equivalent local currency of the departure country for each one-way journey for unaccompanied minors</li>
          <li align="left">It is mandatory to produce photo identification at the airport for all unaccompanied minors.</li>
          <li align="left">Guests should complete and sign an <a href="http://www.spicejet.com/pdf/UNMR_Form.pdf">Unaccompanied Minor Form</a> at the departing airports, we will take charge of their custody and on arrival we require the designated recipient to show identification and sign for the UNM's custody.</li>
          <li align="left">During the trip the children will be escorted by the airlines staff throughout the airport processes and seated in the aircraft where our In-flight personnel will keep a watchful eye on them.</li>
          <li align="left">The UNMR will be handed over at the destination only to the authorized individual specified in the UNM form. Photo ID of personnel authorized to take handover of UNMR will be checked.</li>
          <li align="left">Guests aged between 12-16 is a Young Passenger and will be expected to travel alone.</li>
          <li align="left">If the parents/guardians wish their child to be treated as an unaccompanied minor, this can be done. In this case the UNMR procedure will apply. The young passenger is treated with the same care as Unaccompanied Minors.</li>
          <li align="left">However, a Young Passenger cannot be held responsible for 5-12 years old child, who will be treated as UNMR.</li>
        </ul>
      </dd>
      <dt align="left">+ Carriage of Expectant Mothers:</dt>
      <dt align="left">+ Carriage of Infant Passengers:</dt>
    </dl>
  </div>
